<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.CARB.PT6"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="part" searchtype="LEGISLATION PART" subdoc="false" toc-caption="PART 6 GENERAL PROVISIONS AS TO ARBITRATION">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="true" ln.user-displayed="false">(Repealed)</leg:levelstatus></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading><desig searchtype="PART-NUM"><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CARB.PT6" type="ext"/>PART 6</designum></desig><title searchtype="PART-TITLE">GENERAL PROVISIONS AS TO ARBITRATION</title></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.CARB.S50"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="sect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SECT" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[275,430] s 50 Authority of arbitrator or umpire">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CARB.S50" type="ext"/>[275,430]</edpnum><title searchtype="SECT-TITLE">Authority of arbitrator or umpire</title><desig searchtype="SECT-NUM"><designum>50</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>Subject to this Act, the authority of an arbitrator or umpire is, unless a contrary intention is expressed in the arbitration agreement or the parties to the agreement otherwise agree in writing, irrevocable.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.CARB.S51"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="sect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SECT" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[275,435] s 51 Liability of arbitrator or umpire">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CARB.S51" type="ext"/>[275,435]</edpnum><title searchtype="SECT-TITLE">Liability of arbitrator or umpire</title><desig searchtype="SECT-NUM"><designum>51</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>An arbitrator or umpire is not liable for negligence in respect of anything done or omitted to be done by the arbitrator or umpire in the capacity of arbitrator or umpire but is liable for fraud in respect of anything done or omitted to be done in that capacity.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.CARB.S52"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="sect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SECT" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[275,440] s 52 Death of party">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CARB.S52" type="ext"/>[275,440]</edpnum><title searchtype="SECT-TITLE">Death of party</title><desig searchtype="SECT-NUM"><designum>52</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.CARB.S52.1"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subsect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBSECT">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CARB.S52.1" type="ext"/>(1)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>Unless a contrary intention is expressed in the arbitration agreement, where a party to an arbitration agreement dies the agreement shall not be discharged (either as respects the deceased or any other party) and the authority of an arbitrator or umpire shall not be revoked by the death of that party but the agreement shall be enforceable by or against the personal representative of the deceased.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.CARB.S52.2"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subsect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBSECT">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CARB.S52.2" type="ext"/>(2)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>Nothing in 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.CARB.S52.1" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">subsection (1)</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 shall be taken to affect the operation of any enactment or rule of law by virtue of which a right of action is extinguished by the death of a person.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.CARB.S53"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="sect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SECT" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[275,445] s 53 Power to stay court proceedings">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CARB.S53" type="ext"/>[275,445]</edpnum><title searchtype="SECT-TITLE">Power to stay court proceedings</title><desig searchtype="SECT-NUM"><designum>53</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.CARB.S53.1"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subsect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBSECT">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CARB.S53.1" type="ext"/>(1)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>If a party to an arbitration agreement commences proceedings in a court against another party to the arbitration agreement in respect of a matter agreed to be referred to arbitration by the agreement, that other party may, subject to 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.CARB.S53.2" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">subsection (2)</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 , apply to that court to stay the proceedings and that court, if satisfied:</text></p>
<l><li id="UCPN.OL.CARB.S53.1.A"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CARB.S53.1.A" type="ext"/>(a)</lilabel>
<p><text>that there is no sufficient reason why the matter should not be referred to arbitration in accordance with the agreement, and</text></p>
</li>
<li id="UCPN.OL.CARB.S53.1.B"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CARB.S53.1.B" type="ext"/>(b)</lilabel>
<p><text>that the applicant was at the time when the proceedings were commenced and still remains ready and willing to do all things necessary for the proper conduct of the arbitration,</text></p>
</li>
</l>
<p><text>may make an order staying the proceedings and may further give such directions with respect to the future conduct of the arbitration as it thinks fit.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.CARB.S53.2"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subsect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBSECT">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CARB.S53.2" type="ext"/>(2)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>An application under 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.CARB.S53.1" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">subsection (1)</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 shall not, except with the leave of the court in which the proceedings have been commenced, be made after the applicant has delivered pleadings or taken any other step in the proceedings other than the entry of an appearance.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.CARB.S53.3"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subsect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBSECT">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CARB.S53.3" type="ext"/>(3)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>Notwithstanding any rule of law to the contrary, a party to an arbitration agreement shall not be entitled to recover damages in any court from another party to the agreement by reason that that other party takes proceedings in a court in respect of the matter agreed to be referred to arbitration by the arbitration agreement.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:bodytext>
<leg:comntry subdoc="true" toc-caption="NOTES"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><title><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CARB.S53.COM1" type="ext"/>NOTES</title></heading>
<level id="UCPN_OL.SGM_UCPN.OL.275445-5" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[275,445.5] Stay of proceedings">
<glp:note><blockquote><hrule/>
<p>
<text><inlineobject attachment="web-server" filename="leg1.gif" type="image"/> Legislation cited in [275,445.5] below. LawNow subscribers click through for daily updates and historical versions.</text><text> </text>
<text>(NSW) <ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink alttext="Click to link to LawNow Legislation" dpsi="005Y" refpt="NSW_ACT_1984-160" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Commercial Arbitration Act 1984</remotelink> s 53, s 53(1)(a).</ci:content></ci:cite></text>
</p></blockquote></glp:note><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.275445-5" type="ext"/>[275,445.5] </edpnum><title>Stay of proceedings</title></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text><ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.CARB.S53" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Section 53</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 does not entitle the court, of its own motion, to stay proceedings where there is an arbitration agreement encompassing the relevant dispute: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1992"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000198" spanref="cr000198-001"><ci:reporter value="NSWLR"/><ci:volume num="27"/><ci:page num="299"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">McCaffrey v Port Stephens Shire Council</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000198-001">(1992) 27 NSWLR 299</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="39923" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite> . In considering an application for a stay there is a bias in favour of upholding the provisions of the arbitration agreement between the parties and, prima facie, the courts should hold parties to their bargains: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1911"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000199" spanref="cr000199-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="AC"/><ci:edition><ci:date year="1913"/></ci:edition><ci:page num="241"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref anaphref="cr000199" spanref="cr000199-002" status="unval"><ci:pinpoint num="259" targettype="page"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref ID="cr000200" spanref="cr000200-003" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="AllERRep"/><ci:volume num="13"/><ci:page num="1076"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref anaphref="cr000200" spanref="cr000200-004" status="unval"><ci:pinpoint num="1082" targettype="page"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Bristol Corp v John Aird &amp; Co</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000199-001" status="unval">[1913] AC 241</ci:span> <ci:span spanid="cr000199-002" status="unval">at 259</ci:span>; <ci:span spanid="cr000200-003" status="unval">[1911&#x2013;13] All ER Rep 1076</ci:span> <ci:span spanid="cr000200-004" status="unval">at 1082</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="4369" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite> ; <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1873"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000201" spanref="cr000201-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="CHAPP"/><ci:volume num="LR 8"/><ci:page num="473"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref anaphref="cr000201" spanref="cr000201-002" status="unval"><ci:pinpoint num="480" targettype="page"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Willesford v Wason</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000201-001" status="unval">(1873) LR 8 Ch App 473</ci:span> <ci:span spanid="cr000201-002" status="unval">at 480</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite> ; <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1985"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000202" spanref="cr000202-001"><ci:reporter value="NSWLR"/><ci:volume num="4"/><ci:page num="113"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Qantas Airways Ltd v Dillingham Corp</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000202-001">(1985) 4 NSWLR 113</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite> . However, &quot;sufficient reason&quot; in terms of 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.CARB.S53.1.A" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">s 53(1)(a)</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 may be found in a number of ways &#x2014; including the fact that some only of the parties to the proceedings are parties to the arbitration agreement: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr000203" spanref="cr000203-001"><ci:reporter value="All ER"/><ci:volume num="2"/><ci:edition><ci:date year="1964"/></ci:edition><ci:page num="332"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref ID="cr000204" spanref="cr000204-002" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="WLR"/><ci:volume num="1"/><ci:edition><ci:date year="1996"/></ci:edition><ci:page num="633"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Taunton-Collins v Cromie</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000203-001">[1964] 2 All ER 332</ci:span>; <ci:span spanid="cr000204-002" status="unval">[1964] 1 WLR 633</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite> ; <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr000205" spanref="cr000205-001"><ci:reporter value="VR"/><ci:edition><ci:date year="1974"/></ci:edition><ci:page num="615"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">WC Thomas &amp; Sons Pty Ltd v Bunge (Aust) Pty Ltd</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000205-001">[1974] VR 615</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="102364" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite> ; <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr000206" spanref="cr000206-001"><ci:reporter value="All ER"/><ci:volume num="3"/><ci:edition><ci:date year="1974"/></ci:edition><ci:page num="307"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref ID="cr000207" spanref="cr000207-002" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="WLR"/><ci:volume num="1"/><ci:edition><ci:date year="1975"/></ci:edition><ci:page num="83"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">The Eschersheim</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000206-001">[1974] 3 All ER 307</ci:span>; <ci:span spanid="cr000207-002" status="unval">[1975] 1 WLR 83</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite> ; <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1987"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000208" spanref="cr000208-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="FCR"/><ci:volume num="14"/><ci:page num="193"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref anaphref="cr000208" spanref="cr000208-002"><ci:pinpoint num="209" targettype="page"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref ID="cr000209" spanref="cr000209-003"><ci:reporter value="ALR"/><ci:volume num="71"/><ci:page num="615"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Bond Corp Pty Ltd v Thiess Contractors Pty Ltd</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000208-001" status="unval">(1987) 14 FCR 193</ci:span> <ci:span spanid="cr000208-002">at 209&#x2013;11</ci:span>; <ci:span spanid="cr000209-003">71 ALR 615</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="931" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite> ; <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr000210" spanref="cr000210-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="urj"/><ci:refnum num=" BC9506807"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Alto Constructions Pty Ltd v University of New South Wales</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000210-001" status="unval"> (NSWSC, Young J, 2549/95, 15 December 1995, unreported, BC9506807)</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite> ; <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="2001"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000211" spanref="cr000211-001"><ci:reporter value="NSWLR"/><ci:volume num="52"/><ci:page num="587"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref ID="cr000212" spanref="cr000212-002"><ci:reporter value="urj"/><ci:refnum num="BC200103967"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Savcor Pty Ltd v New South Wales</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000211-001">(2001) 52 NSWLR 587</ci:span>; [2001] NSWSC 596; <ci:span spanid="cr000212-002"> BC200103967</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="331142" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>  (dispute involving another party likely to be the subject of proceedings in any event). This objection may, to a certain extent, be ameliorated by the court's ability to refer related proceedings involving non-parties to the arbitration agreement to a referee who may be the same as the arbitrator appointed pursuant to the arbitration agreement: see <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr000213" spanref="cr000213-000" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="NSWLR"/><ci:volume num="4"/><ci:edition><ci:date year="1985"/></ci:edition><ci:pinpoint num="121" targettype="page"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Qantas Airways Ltd v Dillingham Corp</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF">, <emph typestyle="it">above,</emph><ci:span spanid="cr000213-000" status="unval">at 121&#x2013;2</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite> ; and see 
<remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.SC.20-155-5" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID" status="unval">[20.15.5]</remotelink>
 .</text></p>
</bodytext>
</level><level id="UCPN_OL.SGM_UCPN.OL.275445-10" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[275,445.10] Arbitration agreement">
<glp:note><blockquote><hrule/>
<p>
<text><inlineobject attachment="web-server" filename="leg1.gif" type="image"/> Legislation cited in [275,445.10] below. LawNow subscribers click through for daily updates and historical versions.</text><text> </text>
<text>(NSW) <ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink alttext="Click to link to LawNow Legislation" dpsi="005Y" refpt="NSW_ACT_1984-160" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Commercial Arbitration Act 1984</remotelink> s 4.</ci:content></ci:cite></text>
</p></blockquote></glp:note><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.275445-10" type="ext"/>[275,445.10] </edpnum><title>Arbitration agreement</title></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>If the parties to a contract have agreed that disputes are to be referred to arbitration if one of them so elects, then that agreement is aptly described as an agreement to refer disputes to arbitration, and therefore within the definition of an arbitration agreement: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1991"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000214" spanref="cr000214-001"><ci:reporter value="NSWLR"/><ci:volume num="25"/><ci:page num="54"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Allied Constructions Pty Ltd v Novacoal Australia Pty Ltd</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000214-001">(1991) 25 NSWLR 54</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="34473" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite> ; <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1992"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000215" spanref="cr000215-001"><ci:reporter value="NSWLR"/><ci:volume num="27"/><ci:page num="592"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Turner Corp Ltd v Austotel Pty Ltd</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000215-001">(1992) 27 NSWLR 592</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="39952" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite> . Further, an agreement requiring claims by one party, but not the other, to be submitted to arbitration falls within the definition of an arbitration agreement: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1995"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000216" spanref="cr000216-001"><ci:reporter value="NSWLR"/><ci:volume num="35"/><ci:page num="596"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref anaphref="cr000216" spanref="cr000216-002" status="unval"><ci:pinpoint num="605" targettype="page"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">ABB Power Plants Ltd v Electricity Commission of New South Wales (t/as Pacific Power)</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000216-001">(1995) 35 NSWLR 596</ci:span> <ci:span spanid="cr000216-002" status="unval">at 605</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="103978" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite> . An agreement which gives one or both parties an option to litigate or arbitrate is an &quot;arbitration agreement&quot; within the meaning of 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.CARB.S4" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">s 4</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 : <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1995"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000217" spanref="cr000217-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="CLR"/><ci:volume num="184"/><ci:page num="301"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref ID="cr000218" spanref="cr000218-002"><ci:reporter value="ALR"/><ci:volume num="131"/><ci:page num="377"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">PMT Partners Pty Ltd (in liq) v Australian National Parks &amp; Wildlife Service</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000217-001" status="unval">(1995) 184 CLR 301</ci:span>; <ci:span spanid="cr000218-002">131 ALR 377</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="107899" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite> . The use of the word &quot;may&quot; in an arbitration agreement will not necessarily indicate that such an option to litigate also exists, especially where it appears from the context that arbitration is an alternative to taking no further action or proceedings: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">ABB Power Plants</emph>
</citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite> , above; <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Allied Constructions</emph>
</citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite> , above.</text></p>
</bodytext>
</level><level id="UCPN_OL.SGM_UCPN.OL.275445-15" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[275,445.15] Dispute affecting the validity of the agreement"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.275445-15" type="ext"/>[275,445.15] </edpnum><title>Dispute affecting the validity of the agreement</title></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>Depending upon the terms of the particular arbitration agreement, an arbitrator may be entitled to entertain arguments which affect the validity or enforceability of the contract of which the arbitration agreement itself forms part: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1991"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000219" spanref="cr000219-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="FCR"/><ci:volume num="33"/><ci:page num="227"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref ID="cr000220" spanref="cr000220-002"><ci:reporter value="ALR"/><ci:volume num="105"/><ci:page num="371"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">QH Tours Ltd v Ship Design and Management (Aust) Pty Ltd</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000219-001" status="unval">(1991) 33 FCR 227</ci:span>; <ci:span spanid="cr000220-002">105 ALR 371</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="35108" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite> ; <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1991"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000221" spanref="cr000221-001"><ci:reporter value="NSWLR"/><ci:volume num="22"/><ci:page num="466"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">IBM Australia Ltd v National Distribution Services Pty Ltd</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000221-001">(1991) 22 NSWLR 466</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="23495" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite> . Provided an arbitration clause is drafted widely enough, an arbitrator may determine that a contract is void <emph typestyle="it">ab initio</emph> without depriving himself or herself of jurisdiction: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1994"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000222" spanref="cr000222-001"><ci:reporter value="NSWLR"/><ci:volume num="34"/><ci:page num="474"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Ferris v Plaister</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000222-001">(1994) 34 NSWLR 474</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite> ; see also <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1997"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000223" spanref="cr000223-001"><ci:reporter value="NSWLR"/><ci:volume num="41"/><ci:page num="559"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">FAI General Insurance Co Ltd v Ocean Marine Mutual Protection and Indemnity Assn Ltd</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000223-001">(1997) 41 NSWLR 559</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="223593" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite> .</text></p>
</bodytext>
</level><level id="UCPN_OL.SGM_UCPN.OL.275445-20" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[275,445.20] Dispute referred for expert determination"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.275445-20" type="ext"/>[275,445.20] </edpnum><title>Dispute referred for expert determination</title></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>The court has a discretion to stay proceedings brought contrary to contractual provisions providing for expert determination: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr000224" spanref="cr000224-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="AC"/><ci:edition><ci:date year="1993"/></ci:edition><ci:page num="334"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref ID="cr000225" spanref="cr000225-002"><ci:reporter value="All ER"/><ci:volume num="1"/><ci:edition><ci:date year="1993"/></ci:edition><ci:page num="664"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Channel Tunnel Group Ltd v Balfour Beatty Construction Ltd</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000224-001" status="unval">[1993] AC 334</ci:span>; <ci:span spanid="cr000225-002">[1993] 1 All ER 664</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="47695" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite> ; <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr000226" spanref="cr000226-001"><ci:reporter value="urj"/><ci:refnum num="BC9807200"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Badgin Nominees Pty Ltd v Oneida Ltd</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> [1998] VSC 188; <ci:span spanid="cr000226-001"> BC9807200</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="293054" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>  (complexity of the expert's task not a sufficient reason to refuse a stay); <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr000227" spanref="cr000227-001"><ci:reporter value="All ER"/><ci:volume num="2"/><ci:edition><ci:date year="1992"/></ci:edition><ci:page num="170"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref ID="cr000228" spanref="cr000228-002" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="WLR"/><ci:volume num="1"/><ci:edition><ci:date year="1992"/></ci:edition><ci:page num="277"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Jones v Sherwood Computer Services</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000227-001">[1992] 2 All ER 170</ci:span>; <ci:span spanid="cr000228-002" status="unval">[1992] 1 WLR 277</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite>  (applicant for a stay must satisfy the court that continuation of the process of expert determination would cause injustice); <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr000229" spanref="cr000229-001"><ci:reporter value="All ER"/><ci:volume num="3"/><ci:edition><ci:date year="1997"/></ci:edition><ci:page num="540"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Cott UK Ltd v FE Barber Ltd</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000229-001">[1997] 3 All ER 540</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite>  (stay refused &#x2014; no agreed procedure for determination &#x2014; inappropriate expert &#x2014; complex factual and legal matters in dispute); <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="2001"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000230" spanref="cr000230-001"><ci:reporter value="NSWLR"/><ci:volume num="52"/><ci:page num="587"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref anaphref="cr000230" spanref="cr000230-002" status="unval"><ci:pinpoint num="598" targettype="page"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref ID="cr000231" spanref="cr000231-003"><ci:reporter value="urj"/><ci:refnum num="BC200103967"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Savcor Pty Ltd v New South Wales</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000230-001">(2001) 52 NSWLR 587</ci:span> <ci:span spanid="cr000230-002" status="unval">at 598&#x2013;60</ci:span>; [2001] NSWSC 596; <ci:span spanid="cr000231-003"> BC200103967</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="331142" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>  (stay refused where issues in the proceedings were outside the contractual provision for referral); <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr000232" spanref="cr000232-001"><ci:reporter value="urj"/><ci:refnum num="BC9705205"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Fletcher Construction Australia Ltd v MPN Group Pty Ltd</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000232-001"> (NSWSC, Rolfe J, 14 July 1997, unreported, BC9705205)</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite>  (in the absence of contractual agreement about dispute procedures governing determination by the expert they were a matter for the expert to establish); <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="2002"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000233" spanref="cr000233-001"><ci:reporter value="NSWLR"/><ci:volume num="54"/><ci:page num="503"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref ID="cr000234" spanref="cr000234-002"><ci:reporter value="urj"/><ci:refnum num="BC200201579"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref anaphref="cr000234" spanref="cr000234-003"><ci:pinpoint num="29" targettype="para"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">New South Wales v Banabelle Electrical Pty Ltd</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000233-001">(2002) 54 NSWLR 503</ci:span>; [2002] NSWSC 178; <ci:span spanid="cr000234-002"> BC200201579</ci:span> <ci:span spanid="cr000234-003">at [29], [38]</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="344349" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>  (ineffective provisions for nomination of expert, stay refused).</text></p>
</bodytext>
</level><level id="UCPN_OL.SGM_UCPN.OL.275445-25" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[275,445.25] Step in the proceedings"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.275445-25" type="ext"/>[275,445.25] </edpnum><title>Step in the proceedings</title></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>An application to set aside default judgment will not constitute the taking of a step in the proceedings so as to preclude an application for a stay to enforce the arbitration agreement: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr000235" spanref="cr000235-001"><ci:reporter value="All ER"/><ci:volume num="1"/><ci:edition><ci:date year="1940"/></ci:edition><ci:page num="151"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Pitchers Ltd v Plaza (Queensbury) Ltd</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000235-001">[1940] 1 All ER 151</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite> . There appear to be two requirements before conduct in the proceedings will constitute a bar to the enforcement of the arbitration agreement. First, the conduct in question must demonstrate an intention to abandon the right to a stay in favour of allowing the proceedings to continue. Second, the conduct must actually invoke the jurisdiction of the court: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr000236" spanref="cr000236-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="QB"/><ci:edition><ci:date year="2000"/></ci:edition><ci:page num="551"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref anaphref="cr000236" spanref="cr000236-002" status="unval"><ci:pinpoint num="555" targettype="page"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref ID="cr000237" spanref="cr000237-003" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="WLR"/><ci:volume num="3"/><ci:edition><ci:date year="1999"/></ci:edition><ci:page num="322"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Patel v Patel</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000236-001" status="unval">[2000] QB 551</ci:span> <ci:span spanid="cr000236-002" status="unval">at 555G</ci:span>; <ci:span spanid="cr000237-003" status="unval">[1999] 3 WLR 322</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="299201" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite> .</text></p>
</bodytext>
</level></leg:comntry>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.CARB.S54"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="sect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SECT" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[275,450] s 54 Interpleader">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CARB.S54" type="ext"/>[275,450]</edpnum><title searchtype="SECT-TITLE">Interpleader</title><desig searchtype="SECT-NUM"><designum>54</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>Where relief by way of interpleader is granted in any court and it appears to that court that the claims in question are matters to which an arbitration agreement (to which the claimants are parties) applies, the court may, unless it is satisfied that there is sufficient reason why the matters should not be referred to arbitration in accordance with the agreement, make an order directing the issue between the claimants to be determined in accordance with the agreement.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.CARB.S55"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="sect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SECT" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[275,455] s 55 Effect of Scott v Avery clauses">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CARB.S55" type="ext"/>[275,455]</edpnum><title searchtype="SECT-TITLE">Effect of Scott v Avery clauses</title><desig searchtype="SECT-NUM"><designum>55</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.CARB.S55.1"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subsect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBSECT">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CARB.S55.1" type="ext"/>(1)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>Where it is provided (whether in an arbitration agreement or some other agreement, whether oral or written) that arbitration or an award pursuant to arbitration proceedings or the happening of some other event in or in relation to arbitration is a condition precedent to the bringing or maintenance of legal proceedings in respect of a matter or the establishing of a defence to legal proceedings brought in respect of a matter, that provision, notwithstanding that the condition contained in it has not been satisfied:</text></p>
<l><li id="UCPN.OL.CARB.S55.1.A"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CARB.S55.1.A" type="ext"/>(a)</lilabel>
<p><text>shall not operate to prevent:</text></p>
<l><li id="UCPN.OL.CARB.S55.1.A.I"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CARB.S55.1.A.I" type="ext"/>(i)</lilabel>
<p><text>legal proceedings being brought or maintained in respect of that matter, or</text></p>
</li><li id="UCPN.OL.CARB.S55.1.A.II"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CARB.S55.1.A.II" type="ext"/>(ii)</lilabel>
<p><text>a defence being established to legal proceedings brought in respect of that matter, and</text></p>
</li></l></li>
<li id="UCPN.OL.CARB.S55.1.B"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CARB.S55.1.B" type="ext"/>(b)</lilabel>
<p><text>shall, where no arbitration agreement relating to that matter is subsisting between the parties to the provision, be construed as an agreement to refer that matter to arbitration.</text></p>
</li>
</l>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.CARB.S55.2"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subsect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBSECT">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CARB.S55.2" type="ext"/>(2)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text><ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.CARB.S55.1" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Subsection (1)</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 does not apply to an arbitration agreement unless all the parties to the agreement are domiciled or ordinarily resident in Australia at the time the arbitration agreement is entered into.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.CARB.S55.3"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subsect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBSECT">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CARB.S55.3" type="ext"/>(3)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text><ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.CARB.S55.2" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Subsection (2)</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 does not apply to an arbitration agreement that is treated as an arbitration agreement for the purposes of this Act by virtue only of the operation of 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.CARB.S3.4.A" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">section 3(4)(a)</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 .</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level></leg:levelbody></leg:level-vrnt></leg:level></leg:body></LEGDOC>